Voice Pipeline Bug Fix Plan
I audited the entire chain: STT → Triage → Specialist GPT → TTS → MongoDB → Oversight. Here are all the bugs I found and the fixes.

Root Cause Analysis
The core problem — "not identifying symptoms properly" and falling into a dead "I'm not sure, could you explain more?" loop — is caused by three interconnected bugs:

Bug 1: STT returns empty string → Whisper base model is too small
The base Whisper model (74M params) has poor accuracy on noisy or accented speech. When it can't confidently transcribe, it returns "". Line 184 of voice_pipeline.py then replaces empty speech with the fallback "I'm not sure, could you explain more?", which gives GPT-4o nothing useful to work with.

IMPORTANT

Fix: Upgrade the Whisper model from base to small in .env. The small model (244M params) is dramatically more accurate on real speech while still running on CPU in ~2 seconds.

Bug 2: JSON detection in on_token is fragile and breaks mid-conversation
In voice_pipeline.py line 128, the JSON filter checks if not response_so_far and token.strip() == "{". But GPT-4o often starts a conversational turn with whitespace or a newline before the {, which means response_so_far is already non-empty when { arrives. The filter fails, and the TTS tries to read raw JSON syntax aloud — resulting in garbled speech or silence.

IMPORTANT

Fix: Rewrite the JSON filter to check for { anywhere in the accumulated response, not just as the very first non-whitespace token.

Bug 3: _extract_assessment is a greedy JSON parser that triggers on false positives
In specialist_gpt.py line 252-261, the parser does text.find("{") and text.rfind("}"). If the specialist says something like "Your heart rate is 80, which is normal" and GPT-4o wraps any part in curly braces for emphasis, it will try to parse it as JSON, fail silently, and return None — but in some edge cases it could return a partial dict with ready: false that confuses the flow.

IMPORTANT

Fix: Add a minimum-length check and require "ready" key to be present in the parsed JSON before treating it as an assessment.

Additional Issues Found
Bug 4: TTS _SENTENCE_END regex misses question marks followed by newlines
The regex (?<=[.!?])\s+ only splits on whitespace after punctuation. But GPT-4o often puts a ? at the end of a line with a \n, and \s in Python regex does match \n — but the streaming token buffer may not have the newline yet, so the question hangs in the buffer unsaid until flush_buffer().

Fix: Also flush the buffer on \n characters in stream_token().

Bug 5: voice_pipeline.py oversight check threshold is too strict
Line 415: if len(claimants) > 2 means a medication must be prescribed by 3+ specialists to flag as collusion. With only 1-3 specialists per session, this will never trigger.

Fix: Change to > 1 (2+ specialists prescribing the same drug = flag).

Proposed Changes
[MODIFY] .env
Change WHISPER_MODEL=base → WHISPER_MODEL=small
[MODIFY] src/voice/stt.py
Add a spoken confirmation so the patient knows when the mic is hot and when it stopped
[MODIFY] src/voice/tts.py
Fix the sentence buffer to flush on newlines
[MODIFY] src/voice/voice_pipeline.py
Rewrite on_token JSON filter to be robust
Fix oversight collusion threshold from > 2 to > 1
Add a spoken prompt before each mic recording so the patient knows when to speak
[MODIFY] src/agents/specialist_gpt.py
Make _extract_assessment more robust (require "ready" key + minimum length)
Improve the system prompt to explicitly tell GPT-4o to NEVER include { in conversational text
